# Backend Patterns

## Layer flow (strict)

routes → [validate] → controller → service → model → mapper → dto

- Controllers: call service, `res.json(ok(...))` — no DB, no business logic
- Services: business logic, throw typed errors (`ConflictError`, etc.) — no req/res
- Routes: path + method + middleware only
- Mappers: document → response DTO; input DTOs from Zod `z.infer`

## Imports & naming

- Use `@/path/file.js` (ESM requires `.js` extension)
- Import via barrel `index.ts` when available (`@/services/index.js`)
- Files: kebab-case · Exports: camelCase · Classes: PascalCase

## Responses & errors

- Success: `ok(data)` from `@/utils/envelope.js`
- Errors: throw subclasses from `@/errors/index.js` — `new AppError(message, statusCode, code)`
- `error-handler` should respond via envelope helpers (`fail`, `failErrors`)
- Async controllers: wrap with `asyncHandler` from `@/middlewares/async-handler.js`

## Adding a feature

1. validator → model → service → mapper/dto → controller → route
2. Re-export in layer barrel `index.ts`
3. Mount in `app.ts` (future: central `/api/v1` router in `routes/index.ts`)

## Do not

- Put logic in wrong layer
- Commit `.env` or add unrelated dependencies
- Use `fail()` in controllers — throw errors, let `errorHandler` respond
